<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-03-08T14:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-03-08T14:30:00-05:00" n="389" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d389">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00Sonora/150: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Ciudad Juarez</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dye</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">El
                                        Paso, Tex</hi></placeName>., <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-03-08T12:30:00-07:00">March 8, 1929—12:30
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 4:03 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Armistice called. Reliably informed that Roberto Pesquiera flew from
                            Mexico City via San Antonio to advise General Ramos to cross with troops
                            to El Paso and be interned. Ramos now at Mexican Consulate General, El
                            Paso. Casualties reported twenty-seven killed, fifty wounded.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dye</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>